Description: read and report Google Chat task activity
 majordomo reads Google Chat and reports task activity reconstructed from the
 "Created a task for @Person (via Tasks)" messages that the Google Tasks API
 does not return. It reports tasks by assignee, space, and date, and lists
 spaces, people, messages, and threads.
 .
 A fast path reads an existing server-side cache of Chat; a live path reads the
 Chat API directly and decodes tasks itself, so the tool also works without the
 cache. A privacy sieve drops blocked spaces and assignees in the core.
 .
 The command line is the primary interface. An MCP server (majordomo mcp) is a
 secondary interface for AI agents; it needs the mcp Python package, which is
 not yet available as a Debian package, so install it through pip for that mode.
